        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Upload BNK_01_Group_Loan_Portfolio.xlsx to Analyst. Across the Loan Book Summary, NPL Tracker AND Segment Performance tabs, calculate the absolute and percentage move in gross impaired loans by business line over the last 4 quarters in MYR M, identify the 3 segments driving most of the increase, and quantify the provision top-up needed to reach the 80% internal floor. Build (1) a horizontal bar chart of NPL ratio by segment ranked worst to best, and (2) a stacked column chart of Stage 2 vs Stage 3 balances by segment. Flag segments with NPL above 8% as Red, 5% to 8% Amber, below 5% Green. Output a RAG dashboard with both charts embedded and one corrective action per Red segment.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Upload BNK_01_Group_Loan_Portfolio.xlsx and BNK_04_NPL_Recovery_Tracker.xlsx to Analyst. Cross-reference the Covenant Monitor, Credit Rating Watch AND Recovery Pipeline tabs to identify the obligor and sector clusters most likely to migrate to Stage 3 in the next 2 quarters and quantify the exposure in MYR M behind each cluster. Build a waterfall chart showing the projected NPL trajectory from current 6.8% across cure, restructure and write-off paths over 90 days. Present a RAG table with columns Cluster, Exposure MYR M, Migration Risk, Recovery Path, Recommended Action, with the waterfall embedded beneath.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Upload BNK_05_Capital_Adequacy_Report.xlsx to Analyst. Cross-tab analysis across the CET1 Trend, Capital Tile Sheet AND the Loan Book Summary tab in BNK_01_Group_Loan_Portfolio.xlsx: assess whether the 6.8% NPL ratio creates pressure on CET1, leverage ratio, or liquidity coverage and identify the 3 metrics the Board should monitor weekly for the next 8 weeks. Build sparkline trend charts for CET1, leverage ratio and LCR over the last 8 quarters. Flag metrics with immediate escalation risk Red, watchlist Amber, stable Green. Present as a RAG dashboard with the 3 sparklines and a short note on lender and BNM implications.'}
